    <!-- Section 32: Lesson - Dust and Debris Removal Techniques -->
    <div id="section32" class="section hidden">
        <h2>Lesson: Dust and Debris Removal Techniques</h2>
        <p>Master dust and debris removal with these tips:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-star"></i> Opt for microfiber cloths: Microfiber traps dust without pushing it around. Use dry for dusting, damp for wiping, and rinse or swap them often.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-vacuum"></i> Vacuum smartly with attachments: Use a crevice tool for corners and baseboards, and a brush attachment for delicate areas like vents. A HEPA-filter vacuum excels at catching fine dust.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-up"></i> Dust high areas with an extendable tool: Use an extendable duster or vacuum wand for ceilings and walls, working in overlapping strokes.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-trash"></i> Clear debris in stages: Pick up large items (e.g., wood scraps) first, sweep or vacuum smaller bits (like nails), then wipe surfaces for fine dust.</li>
        </ul>
        <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
        <button onclick="nextSection()">Next</button>
    </div>

