    <!-- Section 34: Lesson - Efficiency and Workflow Techniques -->
    <div id="section34" class="section hidden">
        <h2>Lesson: Efficiency and Workflow Techniques</h2>
        <p>Work smarter with these strategies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-fill-drip"></i> Try the two-bucket mopping method: Use one bucket for clean water and solution, another for dirty water. This keeps your mop effective and floors cleaner.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-arrows-alt-h"></i> Overlap your strokes: When vacuuming, mopping, or wiping, overlap each pass slightly to avoid missing spots.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Clean in a consistent pattern: Move clockwise or counterclockwise around each room to stay systematic and thorough.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-tasks"></i> Multitask during drying: While a floor dries, wipe counters or dust shelves to maximize your time.</li>
        </ul>
        <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
        <button onclick="nextSection()">Next</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 35: Lesson - Safety and Quality Control Techniques -->
    <div id="section35" class="section hidden">
        <h2>Lesson: Safety and Quality Control Techniques</h2>
        <p>Ensure safety and a high-quality finish:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-wind"></i> Keep the space ventilated: Open windows and doors, especially when using chemicals or stirring up dust, to improve air quality.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Inspect with a flashlight: Shine a light at an angle across surfaces to spot hidden dust or smudges for a flawless finish.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-hand-paper"></i> Do a touch test: Run your hand over surfaces—if you feel grit or see residue, keep cleaning.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-camera"></i> Take before-and-after photos: Photos help you track progress and spot areas needing more work during a final check.</li>
        </ul>
        <button onclick="prevSection()">Back</button>
        <button onclick="nextSection()">Next</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Section 36: Lesson - Bonus Pro Tips -->
    <div id="section36" class="section hidden">
        <h2>Lesson: Bonus Pro Tips</h2>
        <p>Elevate your skills with these expert tips:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-window-restore"></i> Squeegee glass surfaces: After cleaning windows or mirrors, use a squeegee for a streak-free shine. Wipe the blade between passes.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-magnet"></i> Use a magnetic sweeper: Quickly collect nails, screws, or metal debris with a magnetic tool to save time and enhance safety.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-toothbrush"></i> Detail with a small brush: A toothbrush or scrub brush cleans tight spots like window tracks or grout with precision.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-wind"></i> Let surfaces air dry: For streak-free floors, glass, or mirrors, allow air drying when possible, touching up with a dry microfiber cloth if needed.</li>
        </ul>
